            If you wish to find all material available in a certain path, leave the search term empty and click "Search."
        </para><para>
            Searching in itself should be fairly obvious. The options are more or less the same as in any library catalogue. In a separate section of this tutorial you can read about the search options at your disposal.
        </para><para>
            If you search for a specific term in the records in the path you have selected or make an "empty search" to retrieve all records in the path you have selected, you will be presented with a list view if more than one record is retrieved.  
        </para><para>
            If you click on any of the hits in the list, you will be taken to the detail view.  
        </para><para><graphic fileref="images/walk-through.07.png" align="center" valign="middle"/></para><para>The format presented in list view attempts to follow <a href="http://www.chicagomanualofstyle.org/home.html" target="_blank">The Chicago Manual of Style</a>.</para></chapter></book>